text.tspan: The motorway ran parallel to a smaller asphault road. I saw a car driving
from the service station on a dirt road to rejoin the smaller road, so made
towards this road. I turned in past a small tent and could see the legs of
more than one reposing persons who stirred as I went past. I parked my
bike and ran up the embankment, lept over the crash barrier and ran over
to the service station shop, bought some snacks and returned to my bike
and went back to the road. A barbed wire barrier had been errected since
I passed the tent and 3 teenagers stood guard.
He said something in arabic that I didnt understand
I looked into his eyes and saw the look which said "because you have so
much more money than I do", I laughed and handed over 1 dirham, he
then demanded another and a handed it over.
Cycled 110km (70 miles) from Ouistreham, France to Alençon, France in
